item.title: UK to quarantine travellers for 14 days
item.description: The British government has told airlines it will introduce a 14-day quarantine period for most people arriving from abroad to try to avoid a second peak of the coronavirus pandemic, an association representing the airlines said on Saturday.

item.title: Shopping crowds raise SA virus complacency
item.description: Thousands of people have flocked to shopping malls and supermarkets across Adelaide, raising concerns of growing complacency over the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Cyclist injured in stolen Mercedes hit-run
item.description: A driver who smashed into a female cyclist, injuring her badly, then drove off should hand himself in, police say.

item.title: Aide to US VP Pence has coronavirus
item.description: Vice President Mike Pence's press secretary has the coronavirus, the White House says, making her the second person who works at the White House complex known to test positive for the virus this week.

item.title: Take care with mum on Mother’s Day
item.description: Australians are being warned to take care when visiting their mums on Mother's Day, particularly if they are elderly.

item.title: Roy from Vegas duo Siegfried and Roy dies
item.description: Magician Roy Horn, who was one half of the German duo "Siegfried & Roy," has died after contracting Covid-19, his spokesman says.

item.title: Latest Newmarch resident death not virus
item.description: A resident who died in Sydney's Newmarch House had recovered from coronavirus and died of an unrelated illness, NSW Health says.

item.title: Zero cases as Qld eases virus restrictions
item.description: Queensland has recorded its third day of zero cases this week but authorities warn the virus has not been eradicated and more cases are expected.

item.title: WA to establish COVID-19 research fund
item.description: Western Australia will establish a multi-million-dollar fund to boost research into the coronavirus and to ramp up the state's testing regime.

item.title: Vic premier considers COVID-19 changes
item.description: As Victorians wait to learn what freedoms will return after the weekend, the state's number of confirmed coronavirus cases has risen again.
